Class Combinations

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<Vector>
        • gov.sandia.cognition.math.Combinations
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloneableSerializable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<Vector>, java.util.Collection<Vector>, java.util.Set<Vector>

    public class Combinations
extends java.util.AbstractSet<Vector>
implements CloneableSerializable
    Enumerates all the combinations on a given number of items sampled from a larger set without considering order, that is, (1,2) is the same as (2,1). For example, there are 3 ways to choose 2 objects from a set of 3: (1,2), (1,3), (2,3).
    Since:
    3.4.2
    Author:
    Kevin R. Dixon
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
